    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but resting isn't enough. the fog is so heavy it feels like it's actually part of me now. i look back at the path i've traveled and i don't even recognize the person who started walking. it's like the journey wasn't meant to reach a destination, it was just meant to wear me down until this exact spot. there's no clearing ahead. just the edge.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
